subSubSection.paragraph:
In addition to the other dimorphic characters (see the variation section for
H. gutui
), the following characters in each sex may be consistently dimorphic: the pereopod 1 basis has two ventrodistal short simple setae in males, one in females; the pereopod 4 basis bears two mid-ventral simple setae in males, none in females; the article 2 of the antennule has two mid-inner simple setae in males, one in females.
